# BROWSER-post.md - IH Post Creation Patterns

All calls require `profile: "{{browser_profile}}"`. Never use `args` in evaluate — inline via template literals.

## Selectors

| Element | Selector | Notes |
|---------|----------|-------|
| Title field | `textarea.post-page__title-field` | maxlength=140, Ember textarea |
| Body field | `textarea.edit-post__body-field` | maxlength=100000, Ember textarea, supports Markdown |
| Group selector trigger | `.group-selector__trigger` | Click to open dropdown |
| Group selector collapsed | `.group-selector--collapsed` | Check before clicking |
| Submit button | `.post-page__submit-button` | Disabled until title+body filled |
| Save draft button | `.post-page__save-draft` | Always enabled |
| Preview toggle | `.post-page__preview-toggle` | |

## ❌ Anti-Patterns

- **NEVER use snapshot + click refs on nav links** — clicking "Starting Up" etc. navigates AWAY from /new-post
- **NEVER look for a category selector** — IH only has group selector (and account may not have groups)
- **NEVER confuse cookie consent with post categories** — `.category-switch-handler` and `.category-filter-handler` are OneTrust cookie consent checkboxes, NOT IH post categories
- **NEVER enumerate all buttons** with `querySelectorAll('button')` — the submit selector is `.post-page__submit-button`, use it directly
- **NEVER explore DOM** with `innerHTML.slice()` — all selectors are documented above
- **NO TipTap/ProseMirror editor on post page** — body is a plain `<textarea>`, not contenteditable
- Group selector shows "You haven't joined any groups" — skip it, post to general feed

## S 7. Create and Submit Post

```javascript
// Step 1: Set title (Ember textarea — use .value + input event)
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `() => {
    var titleArea = document.querySelector('textarea.post-page__title-field');
    if (!titleArea) return { error: 'title_field_not_found' };
    titleArea.focus();
    titleArea.value = '${postTitle}';
    titleArea.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true }));
    titleArea.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true }));
    return { success: true, titleLen: titleArea.value.length };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

```javascript
// Step 2: Set body (Ember textarea — use .value + input event)
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `() => {
    var bodyArea = document.querySelector('textarea.edit-post__body-field');
    if (!bodyArea) return { error: 'body_field_not_found' };
    bodyArea.focus();
    bodyArea.value = '${postBody}';
    bodyArea.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true }));
    bodyArea.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true }));
    return { success: true, bodyLen: bodyArea.value.length };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

```javascript
// Step 3: Wait 500ms for Ember state, then check + click submit
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `() => {
    return new Promise(function(resolve) {
      setTimeout(function() {
        var submitBtn = document.querySelector('.post-page__submit-button');
        if (!submitBtn) return resolve({ error: 'submit_button_not_found' });
        if (submitBtn.disabled) return resolve({ error: 'submit_disabled', hint: 'title or body may be empty' });
        submitBtn.click();
        resolve({ success: true });
      }, 500);
    });
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

```javascript
// Step 4: Wait 4s, verify URL changed from /new-post to /post/slug
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `() => {
    return new Promise(function(resolve) {
      setTimeout(function() {
        resolve({
          url: location.href,
          isPublished: !location.href.includes('/new-post'),
          title: document.title
        });
      }, 4000);
    });
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

If `isPublished: false` after step 4: retry submit once. If still fails, return HEARTBEAT_BLOCKED.

## S 8. Dismiss Cookie Banner (if present)

Run once at browser startup, before any post interaction:

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `() => {
    var acceptBtn = document.querySelector('#onetrust-accept-btn-handler');
    if (acceptBtn) { acceptBtn.click(); return { dismissed: true }; }
    return { noBanner: true };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```
